name: Mother cat and her six kittens, part 5
description:
This recording, encoded in VBR format, is three hours and 10 minutes long.
Like the other recordings in this sound pack, the mother cat and her kittens are inside a nesting box in the garage. A small stereo microphone (Olympus ME51s) was placed inside the brooding area. After editing, they were exported to MP3 format.
Sounds include mewing, purring, shuffling, and nursing. Some occasional heartbeats may be heard as the mother cat or kittens move inside. Other sounds include a rooster crowing, and people working outside, and some occasional people talking in the background.
At this stage, the kittens are in week 3 of their life.

name: Mother cat and her six kittens, part 1
description:
Welcome to the first recording of the series. 
This recording, encoded in VBR format, is one hour and 53 minutes long.
It starts out by introducing the mother cat when she was a kitten herself, probably between eight to ten weeks. Then it shows some occasional sounds of mating and catterwall sound. A recording of the actual birthing process could not be taken as it wasn't known where the queen was going to deliver her litter. She was almost one year old when she had them.
Like the other recordings in this sound pack, the mother cat and her kittens are inside a nesting box in the garage. A small stereo microphone (Olympus ME51s) was placed inside the brooding area. After editing, they were exported to MP3 format.
Sounds include mewing, purring, shuffling, nursing, and mother cat eating dry kibble. Some occasional heartbeats may be heard as the mother cat or kittens move inside. Other sounds include a rooster crowing, and people working outside, and some occasional people talking in the background.
At this stage, the kittens are in week 2 of their life.

name: far river and field 620am 210812_0308.flac
description: Sunrise over the summer fields in Lage Zwaluwe, The Netherlands. The sun is now rising on farmland near a village and 1 km from the estuary at the Hollands Diep and the Amer in the Netherlands. The ship's engines in the distance can be heard like a soft hum in the background. The dove is singing and the rooster is awake. Different kinds of seagulls fly and call here. Sometimes they are close. Also geese calling. The first local traffic comes up, but does not sound disturbing. At half past six you hear the church bell strike once. Birds I determinate: Mallard, Eurasian Jackdaw, Carrion Crow, Herring Gull, Yellow-legged Gull and Mew Gull.
